# Nessus

1. Overview
Nessus is one of the most widely used vulnerability scanners.  
It performs automated scanning to detect vulnerabilities, misconfigurations, outdated services, and security issues across networks, servers, and web applications.

Used in:
- Pentesting  
- Vulnerability assessment  
- Compliance auditing  
- Enterprise security scanning  

---

2. Key Features
- High-quality vulnerability detection  
- Large plugin database (100,000+ checks)  
- Credentialed & non-credentialed scans  
- Compliance & configuration auditing  
- Custom scan templates  
- Exportable reports (HTML, PDF, CSV)  

---

3. Installation

Linux (Debian/Ubuntu)
  1. Download package from official website:  
  https://www.tenable.com/downloads/nessus  

  2. Install:
sudo dpkg -i Nessus-*.deb
sudo systemctl start nessusd
sudo systemctl enable nessusd

RHEL/CentOS
sudo rpm -ivh Nessus-*.rpm
systemctl start nessusd
systemctl enable nessusd

macOS / Windows
Download installer from:
https://www.tenable.com/downloads/nessus

---

4. Access the Web Interface
https://localhost:8834

----

5. Important Parameters & Scan Types
Scan Type	Description
Basic Network Scan	Scan for open ports & vulnerabilities
Advanced Scan	Full customization (plugins, ports, threads)
Web Application Test	Detect OWASP issues
Credentialed Scan	Detect deep OS-level vulnerabilities
Malware Scan	Detect malware indicators

Key Configuration Options:
Port Range: default, all, or custom
Safe Checks: enable/disable
Max Simultaneous Checks
Plugin Selection: family-level or individual

----

6. Advanced Usage
API Usage
curl -k -X GET -H "X-Cookie: token=<token>" https://localhost:8834/scans

Export Scan Results

You can export results in:

HTML

PDF

CSV

Nessus (.nessus) format
